---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Adaptive edge intelligence · Deep Pearl"
  description="A research thread on an assistant that runs on the device, keeps personal data local, and learns from everyday use."
>
  <article class="thread-page wrap">
    <a class="back" href="/#research">
      <span aria-hidden="true">&larr;</span>
      <span>Research</span>
    </a>
    <div class="meta-row">
      <p class="eyebrow"><span class="bar" aria-hidden="true"></span>Research thread</p>
      <span class="tag tag-active">Active prototype</span>
    </div>
    <h1>Adaptive edge intelligence</h1>
    <p class="lede">An assistant that runs on the device, keeps personal data local, and learns from everyday use.</p>

    <div class="thread-body">
      <section class="block">
        <h2>Data stays on the device</h2>
        <p>Personal and biometric signals belong to the person. They are processed locally and never sent away. Local processing is the only honest way to keep that promise.</p>
      </section>
      <section class="block">
        <h2>Layered memory</h2>
        <p>Memory is layered so the system can recall across sessions without sending data away to train. Short context holds the moment. Long context holds the shape of a life. Neither is uploaded.</p>
      </section>
      <section class="block">
        <h2>Signals read together</h2>
        <p>Reading emotion from one signal is brittle. Voice alone is fooled by accent and fatigue. Face alone is fooled by lighting and pose. Several signals together steady each other. The system trusts the agreement, not the loudest input.</p>
      </section>
      <section class="block">
        <h2>Open device layer</h2>
        <p>Building on an open device layer frees the work to focus on the intelligence itself. The platform stops being a moving target. Time goes into models and behavior.</p>
      </section>
    </div>

    <section class="thread-questions">
      <p class="label">Open questions</p>
      <ul>
        <li>How does an assistant get smarter from use without sending data away?</li>
        <li>How much useful intelligence fits on small, low cost hardware?</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>
